## Hi, I'm Shravani 👋

I am a third-year Statistics and Data Science major at UCLA, with a minor in Global Health, originally from San Diego, California. My academic interests include data science, statistical modeling, and applied analytics.

At UCLA, I am involved in Data Science Union, where I collaborate with peers on data-driven projects, and 180 Degrees Consulting, where we work with organizations to address operational and strategic challenges through analytical frameworks.

I previously interned at Warner Music Group, first as a Finance Intern and later as a Data Science Intern within Warner Chappell Music. In these roles, I worked with the Global Digital Finance team on forecasting initiatives and internal analytics tools used to analyze digital music performance. During this experience, I also gained exposure to aspects of music licensing and observed negotiation processes related to digital publishing agreements.

In addition to industry experience, I am involved in research at UCLA in a causal inference lab under Professor Falco Bargagli-Stoffi, where I study statistical methods for causal analysis in complex datasets.

Outside of academics and work, I enjoy music, hiking, being in nature, and dancing.

Below, I have highlighted several projects I have worked on during my time at UCLA.

